message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata and their language recognition capabilities. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for parsing and other basic tasks concerning jumping finite automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper presents several results concerning computational hardness. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) may be relevant as the paper characterizes the class of languages recognized by jumping finite automata in terms of special shuffle expressions, which may involve logical operations. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper deals with language recognition and information processing by finite automata.
